BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 89.28 600 Td (Chapter 1: What is Meal Prepping?) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Meal prepping means preparing some or all of your meals in advance.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (You set aside a few hours each week to cook food for the days ahead.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (This can mean full meals ready to reheat or ingredients prepped for quick cooking.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (There are different levels: full meal prep, ingredient prep, and batch cooking.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Full meal prep means complete meals portioned into containers ready to eat.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Ingredient prep means washing, chopping, and measuring items for faster cooking.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Batch cooking means making large quantities of one recipe to eat all week.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Most meal preppers dedicate Sunday afternoon to cooking for the entire week.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (You do not have to prep every single meal. Even two to three saves significant time.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Meal prepping has exploded in popularity because it works for busy lives.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (It removes the daily stress of deciding what to eat when you are tired.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (By the end of this book you will have a complete system that works for you.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (1) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
