BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 77.75999999999999 600 Td (Chapter 2: Benefits of Meal Prepping) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Save time: cooking once instead of seven times saves hours every week.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Save money: buying in bulk and reducing food waste cuts grocery bills.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Eat healthier: when healthy food is ready, you skip fast food and junk.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Reduce stress: no more staring at the fridge wondering what to make.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Control portions: pre-portioned meals help with weight management goals.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Less food waste: you buy only what you need and use everything you purchase.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (More variety: planning ahead lets you enjoy diverse meals throughout the week.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Better nutrition: you can balance proteins, carbs, and vegetables intentionally.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Fewer dishes: one big cooking session means fewer total pots and pans to wash.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (More free time: weeknight dinners take minutes instead of an hour.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Consistent eating: you are less likely to skip meals when food is ready.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (The average meal prepper saves four to six hours and fifty dollars per week.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (2) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
