q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Choose one day per week as your dedicated cooking day, usually Sunday.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Start with items that take longest: roast meats and bake grains first.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (While proteins cook, wash and chop all vegetables for the week.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Cook multiple items simultaneously using your oven, stovetop, and slow cooker.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Prepare a large batch of grains: rice, quinoa, or pasta for the week.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Roast two to three sheet pans of mixed vegetables at the same time.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Cook two different proteins: perhaps chicken breasts and ground turkey.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Make a big pot of soup or chili that provides four to six servings.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Prepare sauces and dressings in advance to add flavor variety to base meals.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Let everything cool completely before portioning into containers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Label each container with contents and date before refrigerating.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (A typical batch cooking session takes two to three hours for a full week of food.) Tj ET
