BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 100.80000000000001 600 Td (Chapter 7: Storing Food Safely) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Refrigerated meal prep stays fresh for three to four days maximum.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Freeze anything you plan to eat after day four for food safety.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Cool hot food to room temperature within two hours before refrigerating.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Store raw and cooked foods separately to prevent cross-contamination.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Use airtight containers to maintain freshness and prevent freezer burn.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Leave space in containers for frozen food to expand without cracking lids.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Label everything with the date prepared and contents clearly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Most cooked meals freeze well for two to three months without quality loss.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Thaw frozen meals overnight in the refrigerator, not on the counter.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Reheat food to 165 degrees Fahrenheit to ensure safety.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Glass containers are microwave safe and do not stain like plastic.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (When in doubt, throw it out. Food safety is not worth the risk.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (7) Tj ET

endstream
