q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Mistake one: prepping too much food that goes bad before you eat it.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Start small with three to four meals and increase as you find your rhythm.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Mistake two: making the same boring meals every single week.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Rotate recipes and try one new dish weekly to keep things interesting.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Mistake three: not seasoning food well because healthy does not mean bland.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Mistake four: skipping the cooling step and putting hot food in the fridge.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Mistake five: not investing in quality containers that seal properly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Mistake six: overcomplicating recipes instead of keeping meals simple.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Mistake seven: prepping foods that do not reheat or store well.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Avoid prepping fried foods, dressed salads, and crispy items in advance.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Mistake eight: trying to prep every meal instead of just the hardest ones.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Learn from mistakes and adjust your system. Perfection is not the goal.) Tj ET
